.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=863.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: There are no KillSteal/RaidSteal/CampSteal servers</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> This contridicts your above statement. Which is it? Do you feel that the first to the scene has the right? Or first to pull has the right? Because you just stated both. First you say the first to the scene is obviously clearing Juggs and has the right, then you go a different direction and say that racing to the mob is the right way.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
My statements aren't contradictory.  <br>
<br>
The situation at Kalorek`Dar is much more like Lozidal than Trakanon.  Trakanon is about GEOGRAPHY and Lozidal is about READINESS.  If you have a GEOGRAPHICAL advantage on Trakanon (you've passed lower exit and have a magician), most people conceed the camp.  If you have a READINESS advantage on Lozidal (e.g. you have enough people to kill him) then people respect your pull/kite.<br>
<br>
I use two examples to show two different situations where two different sets of &quot;understood&quot; rules apply.  Having 40 people in Sebilis first isn't worth anything if you don't mobilize and get to the mushrooms first.  Similarly, being at Lozidal isn't worth a hill of beans if you aren't ready to kill him.<br>
<br>
I simply submit that Kalorek`Dar is about readiness.  10 Vision players were ready to kill Kalorek`Dar before 20 Divine Legion players were.  Had a Divine Legion puller swam out to Kalorek`Dar and pulled him, no Vision would have interfered; and, if asked, we would have helped.  If Kalorek`Dar had 10 guards that needed cleared, and Divine Legion was clearing them already (like the Trakanon/Juggernaut example), no Vision would have gone near his spawn unless to offer help.  <br>
<br>
Kalorek`Dar has no guards; no Divine Legion puller/tracker was in the water; Vision was ready first.  Vision killed Kalorek`Dar, found my corpse, looted up and headed off to Western Wastes where Scout Charissa was waiting, sans bag.<br>
<br>
Everyone works by these unwritten &quot;understood&quot; rules.  We all know what the Verant rules say, and we all know what the community thinks, and we all have our own values.  The reason that Trakanon is the way Trakanon is, is that the people who kill Trakanon &quot;just do it like that.&quot;  The reason that Lozidal is the way Lozidal is, is that the people who kill Lozidal &quot;just do it like that.&quot;<br>
<br>
The *old* Ragefire is another example that transcends a Grand Unified Theory of Engagement.  As it stood, the &quot;understood&quot; Ragefire camp was that you respect the cleric who spends a weekend waiting for him to spawn, and then he gets a &quot;reasonable although non-quantifiable period of time&quot; to gather the necessary forces to kill Ragefire.<br>
<br>
To each encounter there is an &quot;understood&quot; rule of engagement.  Try asking CB and VV what the rules of engagement for Vulak are when they're both in NToV with Eternal Wrath.<br>
<br>
I think our rules of engagement for &quot;big targets&quot; are fairly conservative, even more restrictive than most guilds of our size, and certainly within what the &quot;community&quot; finds acceptable.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> You entering the zone does not mean that we have to quickly bow down and open communication, like you're &quot;above&quot; opening it with us or something. Superior attitudes really piss me off. We were in force first and medding up to pull, we should not have to drop everything to start a line of communication with you, when you should have opened it with us first.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Two issues here, I'll try to take them seperately.<br>
<br>
First, you keep saying you were there in force.  Numbers don't equate to readiness.  Having more people in a zone doesn't make you any more or any less ready to engage a target.  You say yourself that we had people in the zone while you were gathering.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Well, we were gathing too.  We just gathered the NECESSARY and READY force faster.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Second, as to you who has to ask who...  ...sadly it boils down to this:  If our two guild run into a similar situation, and there is no communication, then it is likely, based on previous events that Vision will end up winning the race.  If our two guilds run into a similar situation, and there <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> IS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> communication, unless you plan on holding a grudge, our guilds will probably end up working together.<br>
<br>
Compare that to us forming up for a mob that Eternal Wrath wants to kill.  Eternal Wrath need not, under any circumstance that I can imagine, ever send us a tell asking for our &quot;permission&quot; to do anything.  On several occasions, we've sent them tells asking to do things with them.  As a result of that, Vision has a nice working relationship with Eternal Wrath.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> [Obviously the comparision between DL &lt; Vision &lt; EW isn't quite linear, but it helps demonstrate my point.]</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
We're faced with two choices, (a) silently race Eternal Wrath and lose, or (b) open dialogs with them and participate.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> when YOU didn't want to work with US.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This is gonna sound harsh, but I want to keep the terms simple.  At present, it benefits YOU more than it benefits US for our guilds to work together.<br>
<br>
Some targets are, and will always be a race.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> It's pure bullshit, and frankly I'm suprised as hell hearing such a hypocritical statement:<br>
<br>
&quot;We'll work with you if you treat us with respect; and if you don't want to work with us, then we'll do our best to beat you to targets fairly and be humble about it when we don't.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I think you should ask around.  Ask Exiled Alliance how last night went, or how Wuoshi has gotten killed recently, or even how we've distributed the loot with them.  Ask Scorcha how her epic is doing.  Ask Warfrost about his shot at a Green Dragonscale.  Ask any of the guilds we helped do an imporant target or assisted in their corpse recoveries.<br>
<br>
Even ToV, whom we butt heads with on a regular basis...  ...ask them, that if nothing else, outside of a few pokes and jabs at each other, if Vision treats them respectfully with regard to competition for spawns.<br>
<br>
I can only close by asking you not to let this sour working with us again. It's throwing out the baby with the bathwater - cutting off your nose to spite your face.<br>
<br>
I think you'll find that we'd be open to raiding any target you wanted to raid together as long as there was something mutually beneficial to be gained.<br>
<br>
If you wish to discuss this further, not in public, than you can reach me by email at mstenge@chw.edu <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4868>Palimax Sceleris</a>,
